 from the past that can usefully be applied to contemporary circumstances. The book outlines how the construction of lessons is tied to the construction of historical memory and demonstrates how histories are constructed to serve the needs of the present. In so doing, it creates a new theory of doctrinal development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCounterinsurgencyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aIraq War, 2003-2011. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xInfluence. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975zUnited States. 4aIraq war. 4aUS Army. 4aVietnam War. 4acollective memory. 4acounterinsurgency. 4adoctrine. 4alesson-learning. 4alessons of Vietnam. 4astrategic culture. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804786423zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804786423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804786423.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles